title: Untitled
content:
#!/bin/sh

interface="$(ip tuntap show | cut -d : -f1 | head -n 1)"
ip="$(ip a s "${interface}" 2>/dev/null \
        | grep -o -P '(?<=inet )[0-9]{1,3}(\.[0-9]{1,3}){3}')"

if [ "${ip}" != "" ]; then
  printf "<icon>network-vpn-symbolic</icon>"
  printf "<txt>${ip}</txt>"
  if command -v xclip; then
    printf "<iconclick>sh -c 'printf ${ip} | xclip -selection clipboard'</iconclick>"
    printf "<txtclick>sh -c 'printf ${ip} | xclip -selection clipboard'</txtclick>"
    printf "<tool>VPN IP (click to copy)</tool>"
  else
    printf "<tool>VPN IP (install xclip to copy to clipboard)</tool>"
  fi
else
  printf "<txt></txt>"
fi

title: OutlookRule
content:
^F2::OutlookRule.addRule()
Class OutlookRule
{
    static __New()
    {
        g := Gui(, "Outlook Rule Creator")
        g.SetFont("s12", "Segoe UI")
        g.AddText("section", "Rule Name:")
        g.editName := g.e1 := g.AddEdit()
        g.t1 := g.AddText("cRed Hidden x+m yp", "*")
        g.AddText("xs", "Keyword(s) in Subject:")
        g.editKeywords := g.e2 := g.AddEdit()
        g.t2 := g.AddText("cRed Hidden x+m yp", "*")
        g.AddText("xs", "Folder Name:")
        g.editFolder := g.e3 := g.AddEdit()
        g.t3 := g.AddText("cRed Hidden x+m yp", "*")
        (g.AddButton("xs", "Create Rule")).OnEvent("Click", (*) => this._checkInput())
        g.onEvent("Close", (*) => this._close())
        g.onEvent("Escape", (*) => this._close())
        this.gui := g
    }
    ; private: basic check if input is valid, highlight errors inn Gui if no, proceed if yes
    static _checkInput()
    {
        warn := [0,0,0]
        this.ruleName := this.gui.editName.value
        ; keywords can be a comma or space separated list of words
        if InStr(this.gui.editKeywords.value, ",")
            this.keywords := StrSplit(this.gui.editKeywords.value, "," , " ")
        else
            this.keywords := StrSplit(this.gui.editKeywords.value, " ")
        this.Folder := this.gui.editFolder.value
        if !this.ruleName 
            warn[1] := true
        if !this.keywords.has(1)
            warn[2] := true
        if !this.folder
            warn[3] := true

        for k, v in warn
        {
            if v
                this.gui.t%k%.Visible := 1, fail := true
            else
                this.gui.t%k%.Visible := 0
        }
        if IsSet(fail)
        {
            Loop warn.length
            {
                if warn[A_Index]
                {
                    this.gui.e%A_Index%.Focus()
                    break
                }
            }
            this.gui.Show("AutoSize")
            color := this.gui.BackColor, this.gui.BackColor := "red"
            SetTimer((*) => this.gui.BackColor := color, -150)
            this.gui.flash
            SoundPlay("*64")
            return
        }
        else
        {
            this._resetGui()
            this._createRule()
        }
    }
    ; private: reset vaules in the gui edit fields
    static _resetGui()
    {
        this.gui.editName.value := ""
        this.gui.editKeywords.value := ""
        this.gui.editfolder.value := ""
    }
    ; private: hide gui and & reset edit fields
    static _close()
    {
        this._resetGui()
        this.gui.hide
    }
    ; public: show gui for user to enter a new rule
    static addRule()
    {
        this.gui.Show("Autosize")
        this.gui.editName.Focus()
    }
    ; private: create a new rule based on the last gui input (newrule, keywords, folder)
    static _createRule()
    {
        static VT_BSTR := 0x8
        static olRuleReceive := 0x0, olRuleSend := 0x1
        try
            outlook := ComObjActive("Outlook.Application"), o := true
        catch
            outlook := ComObject("Outlook.Application"), o := true
        finally 
        {
            if !IsSet(o)
                MSgBox("Unable to start Outlook!")
        }
        try
        {
            rules := outlook.Session.DefaultStore.GetRules()
            newRule := Rules.Create(this.ruleName, olRuleReceive)
            keywords := ComObjArray(VT_BSTR, this.keywords.length)
            ; SafeArrays start w/ index 0
            for k, v in this.keywords
                keywords[k-1] := v
            condition := newRule.Conditions.Subject
            condition.Text := keywords
            condition.Enabled := true
            action := newRule.Actions.MoveToFolder
            try
                Action.Folder := outlook.Application.Session.Folders.Item("m.haubrich@jenato.com").Folders.Item(this.folder)
            catch
                Action.Folder := outlook.Application.Session.Folders.Item("m.haubrich@jenato.com").Folders.Add(this.folder)
            action.Enabled := true
            newRule := true
            rules.Save()
            SoundPlay("*-1")
            ToolTip("Created new rule!")
            SetTimer((*) => ToolTip(), -2000)
        }
        catch Error as e
        {
            MsgBox("Unable to create new rule!`nError on Line" e.Line "`n`n" e.Message)
        }
    }
}
